[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":264},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F19\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F19\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F19\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F19\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands\u002F":241,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F19\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands\u002F":250},"\u002Fhexo\u002F20200919\u002F55362084\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":224,"date":225,"description":19,"extension":226,"lang":227,"meta":228,"navigation":229,"path":230,"readingMinutes":231,"seo":232,"standalone":233,"stem":234,"tags":235,"tldr":238,"updated":225,"url":239,"__hash__":240},"content\u002Fen\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands.md","(6) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Hexo Commands You Can't Forget","4802635501",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":210},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,44,48,51,80,94,99,102,106,120,127,133,143,149,155,159,165,171,178,181,185,197,201,207],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This post walks through the more important Hexo commands. We've actually touched a few of them already in earlier posts, so here I'll bring them all together in one place.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"commands-you-can-forget","Commands you can forget",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"You're probably thinking — wait, the title says \"Hexo Commands You Can't Forget\", why is the first section about commands you ",[28,29,30],"em",{},"can"," forget? The thing is, you'll only ever use these a single time, so you can genuinely forget they exist and just look them up again when you actually need them.",[17,33,34,35,39,40,43],{},"The forgettable ones are ",[36,37,38],"code",{},"hexo init [folder-name]"," and ",[36,41,42],{},"hexo -v",". The first you only run once when you create a project, and the second you only really need when checking your version or filing a bug report.",[12,45,47],{"id":46},"the-hexo-commands-you-cant-forget","The Hexo commands you can't forget",[17,49,50],{},"Now for the important ones — the Hexo commands you really shouldn't forget:",[52,53,54,60,65,70,75],"ul",{},[55,56,57],"li",{},[36,58,59],{},"hexo new 'article-name'",[55,61,62],{},[36,63,64],{},"hexo generate",[55,66,67],{},[36,68,69],{},"hexo server",[55,71,72],{},[36,73,74],{},"hexo clean",[55,76,77],{},[36,78,79],{},"hexo deploy",[17,81,82,83,86,87,86,90,93],{},"Hexo actually has quite a few more commands — ",[36,84,85],{},"hexo list",", ",[36,88,89],{},"hexo migrate",[36,91,92],{},"hexo publish",", etc. — but in practice you really only use the five above. So these five are the ones you'll be running constantly.",[95,96,98],"h3",{"id":97},"creating-a-new-post","Creating a new post",[17,100,101],{},"We already tried this one earlier, so I'll skip the details.",[95,103,105],{"id":104},"generating-static-files","Generating static files",[17,107,108,109,111,112,115,116,119],{},"When you run ",[36,110,64],{},", Hexo compiles your ",[36,113,114],{},"source"," files against the theme and produces static files. You'll see the terminal start compiling, and a new ",[36,117,118],{},"public"," folder will appear at the root of the project.",[17,121,122],{},[123,124],"img",{"alt":125,"src":126},"Static files","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-18%2015.33.52.png",[17,128,129,130,132],{},"That ",[36,131,118],{}," folder is your blog.",[17,134,135,136,138,139,142],{},"You can drag ",[36,137,118],{}," into VSCode and open it with the Preview on Web Server or Live Server extension. I'll use Preview on Web Server for the demo (and I'd recommend running it on ",[36,140,141],{},"index.html",").",[17,144,145],{},[123,146],{"alt":147,"src":148},"Preview on Web Server","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-18%2015.40.04.png",[17,150,151],{},[123,152],{"alt":153,"src":154},"Your blog","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002FJavaScript%20%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E8%A7%80%E5%BF%B5\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-18%2015.40.15.png",[12,156,158],{"id":157},"spin-up-the-dev-server","Spin up the dev server",[17,160,161,162,164],{},"Using Preview on Web Server or Live Server works, but it's kind of annoying. Hexo has its own built-in dev server — just run ",[36,163,69],{}," and once it's up you'll see the info in the terminal:",[17,166,167],{},[123,168],{"alt":169,"src":170},"Dev server","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-18%2015.45.57.png",[17,172,173,174,177],{},"When you see this, click ",[36,175,176],{},"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost:4000"," or just open it in your browser.",[17,179,180],{},"You might wonder how to stop the server — just hit Ctrl + C twice (same on Windows).",[12,182,184],{"id":183},"clearing-cache","Clearing cache",[17,186,187,188,190,191,194,195,142],{},"Sometimes you'll hit weird issues. Running ",[36,189,74],{}," usually fixes them. It clears the cache file (",[36,192,193],{},"db.json",") and the compiled output (",[36,196,118],{},[12,198,200],{"id":199},"deploying-static-files","Deploying static files",[17,202,203,204,206],{},"Last one — ",[36,205,79],{},". Just know it exists for now. We'll use it in a later post to deploy to GitHub Pages, and I'll cover it properly then.",[17,208,209],{},"That's it for today's Ironman post. The list of commands might look intimidating at first, but if you're writing posts regularly, these really aren't a big deal.",{"title":211,"searchDepth":212,"depth":212,"links":213},"",2,[214,215,216,221,222,223],{"id":14,"depth":212,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":212,"text":23},{"id":46,"depth":212,"text":47,"children":217},[218,220],{"id":97,"depth":219,"text":98},3,{"id":104,"depth":219,"text":105},{"id":157,"depth":212,"text":158},{"id":183,"depth":212,"text":184},{"id":199,"depth":212,"text":200},"Hexo","2020-09-19 21:16:39","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands","2",{"title":6,"description":19},false,"en\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands",[224,236,237],"Learning Hexo from Scratch","iThome Ironman 2020",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F19\u002Flearn-hexo-06-essential-commands\u002F","Uo1AGcPEpDW80eg9QH9uCgkNokVIxL4M28oCkY1cEXk",{"newer":242,"older":246},{"url":243,"title":244,"date":245},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F20\u002Flearn-hexo-07-installing-plugins\u002F","(7) Learning Hexo from Scratch - How to Install Plugins","2020-09-20 00:01:10",{"url":247,"title":248,"date":249},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F18\u002Flearn-hexo-05-your-first-post\u002F","(5) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Your First Post","2020-09-18 08:20:55",[251,255,260],{"url":252,"title":253,"date":254,"readingMinutes":231},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F30\u002Ffix-hexo-updated-date-on-ci-deploy\u002F","Fix: All Posts Show Updated Date After Hexo Upgrade or CI Deploy","2022-10-30 11:52:35",{"url":256,"title":257,"date":258,"readingMinutes":259},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F11\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-33-updating-next-theme\u002F","(33) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Extras: Updating the NexT Theme","2020-11-01 13:21:00","3",{"url":261,"title":262,"date":263,"readingMinutes":231},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F31\u002Flearn-hexo-32-updating-hexo\u002F","(32) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Extras: Updating Hexo","2020-10-31 14:01:51",1784012773783]